<br>
If something is in melee with you (even if they are shooting missle weapons at you) any attack, hit or miss, will interrupt your casting. In DAoC you simply cannot cast while in direct combat.<br>
<br>
Now, that said, there are exceptions to that rule.<br>
<br>
#1) Some spells are insta-cast. You click, it's cast, that's it. Most spells like this (a dn indeed almost all classes of pwoerful spells) have a reuse timer on them of 10+ seconds, so you cannot chain cast the insta-cast spells.<br>
<br>
#2) If you have quickcast, you can use it to make any spell insta-cast. Quickcast itself has an 18-second reuse timer, and takes a chunk of your stamina away as well as a little extra power when the spell is cast.<br>
<br>
That's all I know about it so far as a 10 Wizzy... <p>Raviel Darkfyre<BR>
